StoryAsset.name: PreMatch League Match Up User Lower

keyValuePair.Value: A big, big game. Who'll win?
This is a real six-pointer at the top against %1s. How have your preparations been going? Are you confident your team can come out with the victory?
At our best, we'll beat anybody.
This is an excellent group of players and we've got plenty of self-belief. I'm absolutely sure that, if we're at our best, we can win any game. Including this one!
I think we're ready to win this.
The boys have been working flat-out in training. They're really up for this game. It'll be tight but I think our confidence and team spirit can give us the edge here.
The boys have been working flat-out in training. They're really up for this game. It'll be tight but I think our confidence and team spirit can give us the edge here.
This isn't the time for predictions.
I'll leave it to other people to speculate about who's going to win. My job is to get the boys into the very best shape for the game. We'll go out there and play and do our talking afterwards.
Can you get your lads believing?
You're up against the team in second and I'm sure you want to make up ground on them in the table. What's the mood in your dressing room? Have you got the boys fired up for the game?
Look at the table. There's the motivation.
Playing a very good team who are ahead of us in the table is all the motivation my players need. They know what's at stake. We can't wait for the game.
We'll be strong, I promise you.
These players are excellent professionals. I have no doubts at all about their mentality. They know what a win would mean and will go all-out to get it.
These lads are always ready!
I'm very lucky. I have a highly-motivated group of players here. I try to give them information and a plan. Their attitude is something I never have to worry about.
Do you have any chance against the league leaders?
A look at the table would say you've got no chance, with %2s sitting last up against %1s, the team leading the league. Do you think your team's capable of pulling off a surprise result?
We can do something here.
For a team at the top, playing against the bottom side brings its own kind of pressure. I think we've got players who can hurt them. We'll definitely give this game a go.
The important thing is to perform.
Look, of course it won't be easy. We have to focus on being at our best and putting in a proper performance. That's what I'm focused on rather than the result.
Look, of course it won't be easy. We have to focus on being at our best and putting in a proper performance. That's what I'm focused on rather than the result.
%1s being top isn't what we focus on.
Where the opposition are in the table isn't what needs to concern us. We're in a bad league position, obviously, and getting points is what matters for us now, whoever we're playing against.
Looking forward to the game?
Your %1s side sit in second place and today you're up against the league leaders. What are you expecting? Is this a chance for your boys to throw the title race wide open?
We've been looking forward to this game.
We're definitely in the hunt for the title. This game against the leaders is a chance to make up ground and to show what we're capable of. We can't wait for kick-off!
We mustn't get carried away.
First of all, win or lose, we mustn't get carried away. We've got to be mentally strong, every player switched on and doing his job for the whole 90 minutes. Then we'll see.
We're bang in form right now.
The way we've been playing recently, I think you could probably make us favourites here. You'd have to say the pressure's all on the leaders today, that's for sure.
Are you worried about a heavy defeat?
You're taking on the team at the top of the table and your recent form has seen you slip to the bottom. They're heavy favourites. Are you worried your boys could get a hammering here?
We'll look to win, regardless.
Once the game kicks off, positions in the league table mean nothing. It's 11 against 11. The lads won't be overawed. We'll go for the win like we always do.
I don't want our confidence damaged.
It looks like a very difficult game for us. We know how good they are, especially going forward. We have to be mentally strong. I don't want a heavy defeat damaging our confidence.
We obviously have a very difficult match on our hands today. Considering the offensive abilities of our opponents, I just hope the boys will not be too disheartened if that happens.
No point making predictions now.
I'm not going to make any predictions. I don't want my players going out there thinking they're already beaten. We'll give it 100%, I promise you. And afterwards we can see where we stand.
I'm not going to make any predictions. I don't want my players going out there thinking they're already beaten. We'll give it 100%, I promise you. And afterwards we can see where we stand.
Can you make a statement against the league leaders?
It's a game to look forward to, taking on %1s, the team at the top of the table. Is this a chance for your players to show what they're capable of? Can you give the leaders a game?
I think we can beat them.
I genuinely think my team's as good as the league leaders. Maybe better. We'll go into the game believing we can get a result. The boys can make a statement here against the leaders.
I think this looks evenly-matched.
I know they're above us in the table but I think this game's wide open. Two very strong teams: we believe we can get the three points and I'm sure the leaders feel the same way.
We'll have to wait and see who comes out on top.
The leaders are top of the table for a reason. %1s are a very good team. But we definitely feel we can do something against them. We'll give 100%, then let's see what happens!
How will you motivate your players today?
Sometimes players look at a game and don't feel the pressure, as if there's not much at stake. How do you plan to get a really committed performance out of your team here?
We have professional standards.
I hope the boys know that every game matters. Points are points, whoever you're playing against. We have to be professional in our approach every time we step onto the field.
I'm not worried about my team.
This is an experienced group of players and one thing you can never fault is their attitude. They know you can't pick and choose when to turn up. This team gives 100% in every single game.
You can't pick and choose your games.
There's something at stake in every single game we play. We can't make judgements on the basis of who we're playing. We have to go out and do our jobs every time, don't we?
